        <div class="privacy-content">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>This Privacy Policy ("Privacy Policy") applies to all who use the website accessible at https://www.volaris.ai (the "Site"), which is owned and operated by Volaris LLC, a Florida limited liability company, and its subsidiaries, representatives, affiliates, officers, and directors (collectively, "Volaris"). For purposes of this Privacy Policy, the words "you" and "your" refer to each individual accessing and using the Site, and "Volaris" may sometimes be referred to herein as "us," "our," or "we." The purpose of this Privacy Policy is to inform you what information we may collect, how we use such information, and who we will share such information with, if at all, when you access and use the Site.</p>
            
            <p>This Privacy Policy does not address the privacy practices of any third parties that we do not own, control, or are affiliated with. By accessing or using the Site, you confirm your agreement to be bound by the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to the Privacy Policy, you may not access or use the Site. This Privacy Policy applies only to our online activities and is valid for visitors to the Site with regard to the information that they share and that we collect on the Site. This Privacy Policy is not applicable to any information collected offline or via channels other than the Site.</p>
            
            <p>We take the privacy concerns of our Site visitors seriously. Therefore, if you have additional questions or require more information about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at team@volaris.ai.</p>

            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>When you access and use our Site, we collect the information that you choose to provide to us. This may include, without limitation, your name, email address, phone number, address, responses to personal or business-related questions, and any message and/or attachments you may send us.</p>
            
            <p>Like most website operators, we also collect non-personally identifying information such as browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor request. Our purpose in collecting this information is to better understand how our visitors use our Site. We may also gather certain information automatically, such as Internet protocol (IP) addresses, browser type, ISP, operating system, and your Site activity (including content viewed, mouse activity, and clickstream data) to analyze trends, administer the Site, and enforce our Terms of Use. We use cookies, web beacons, session replay, and similar technologies to collect this information.</p>
            
            <p>We may also collect precise location data, such as GPS coordinates, cell tower information, or Wi-Fi signals. You can disable location tracking in your device settings if you do not want us to collect this data.</p>

            <h2>Children Under 13</h2>
            <p>Our Site and services are not intended for children under the age of 13. If we learn that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will delete such information immediately.</p>

            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We may use your data to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Send you information, updates, and promotions about the specific product or service you opted into.</li>
                <li>Provide relevant content, offers, and support.</li>
                <li>Improve our websites, ads, and user experience.</li>
                <li>Cross-market other offers or services we own or manage, including those in different verticals (e.g. real estate, e-commerce, investing, digital marketing, AI education, etc.).</li>
                <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce terms.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Cross-Brand Communication & Ownership</h2>
            <p>By submitting your information, you acknowledge and agree that your data may be shared between brands, products, or entities operated by the same owners or management team. You may receive promotional communication from these other businesses, even if you originally opted into a different brand's list. All such communication will contain an option to opt-out at any time.</p>

            <h2>Third-Party Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell your data to unrelated third parties. However, we may share your data with:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Service providers (email, CRM, analytics platforms) to operate our business.</li>
                <li>Joint venture partners or affiliates we are contractually aligned with, if you engage with a co-branded offer or funnel.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Your Rights and Opt-Out</h2>
            <p>You may unsubscribe from emails at any time using the link at the bottom of each message. You may also contact us directly to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Request access to or deletion of your data,</li>
                <li>Ask what information we store,</li>
                <li>Withdraw consent for any future communication.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>How We Share Information</h2>
            <p>We do not sell your information. We may share it as follows:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>With prospective clients: If you've worked with us, we may share limited personal contact info (first name, first initial of last name, phone number, state of residence) for referral purposes.</li>
                <li>With affiliates and selected partners to offer relevant services or promotions</li>
                <li>With vendors performing services on our behalf (e.g., payment processing, fulfillment)</li>
                <li>As required by law or to protect our legal rights, safety, or prevent fraud</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
            <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to improve user experience. You may choose to reject cookies via your browser settings, but this may limit your ability to use certain features of the Site.</p>
            
            <p>Learn more about cookies here: <a href="https://www.cookieconsent.com/what-are-cookies/" target="_blank">https://www.cookieconsent.com/what-are-cookies/</a></p>

            <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
            <p>Our Site may contain links to external websites that are not controlled by us. Please review their respective privacy policies before sharing any personal information. We are not responsible for their actions, content, or privacy practices.</p>

            <h2>Google AdWords for Remarketing</h2>
            <p>We use Google Ads to remarket to users who have visited our Site. This means we may show you ads on Google or its partner sites based on your past interactions. Google and other vendors use cookies for this purpose. You can adjust your ad settings at Google Ad Preferences.</p>

            <h2>Opting-Out From Communications</h2>
            <p>You may opt out of marketing emails or prevent your personal contact information from being shared with prospective clients by emailing us at team@volaris.ai.</p>

            <h2>Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. If changes are significant, we'll notify you via the Site or other means. Continued use of the Site after updates implies your acceptance of the revised policy. We encourage you to review this page regularly.</p>
